All three are required for sustained Resonant-grade field operation. None alone is sufficient.

== Substrate ==

All three modules share a common substrate:
* [[HelmKit]] mount and power.
* Near-field RF emitter architecture (see [[HelmKit Architecture]]).
* Dual-MCU safety supervision.
* Operator-controlled engagement (no involuntary activation).
* Calibration against the operator's measured baseline.

The shared substrate is why the triad lives in the [[HelmKit]] psi-bay: hardware is reused; the function differs in signal pattern, not in physics.

== Public Doctrine ==

* Psi-Tech is defensive and supportive only. There is no offensive psi-weapon in the Clan's line.
* Psi-Tech engages only with the operator's consent and disengages on instability.
* Psi-Tech does not radiate effects on bystanders — it is near-field, single-operator.
* Psi-Tech specifications, safety envelopes, and failure modes are public on the wiki.

